---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Love Not Fear — David Henzel"
  description="Love Not Fear is David Henzel's decision-making framework: every choice comes from love or fear. Learn how leading from love changes how you build, lead, and grow."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-6">Philosophy</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        Love Not Fear
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
        A framework for making better decisions — in your business, your leadership, and your life. Every choice you make comes from one of two places. Which one are you choosing from?
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Core Idea -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <SectionHeading title="The Framework" />
      <div class="space-y-5 text-base text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Every decision you make — how you hire, how you handle conflict, how you treat your team, how you respond when things go wrong — comes from one of two emotional states: love or fear.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fear-driven decisions look like: micromanaging because you don't trust people, avoiding hard conversations because you dread conflict, over-hiring to protect against uncertainty, or staying in a bad situation because change feels too risky.
        </p>
        <p>
          Love-driven decisions look like: giving your team real ownership because you believe in them, having the hard conversation because you genuinely care about the other person's growth, letting go of something that isn't working because you're building something real.
        </p>
        <p>
          The framework isn't about being soft. It's about recognizing which driver is behind your choices — and consciously shifting from one to the other. David developed this through years of building companies, doing his own inner work, and observing patterns in hundreds of founder conversations. The insight kept repeating: the worst decisions came from fear. The best ones came from love.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Principles -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <SectionHeading
      title="Four Principles"
      subtitle="The Love Not Fear framework comes down to four practical commitments."
    />
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">

      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-3">01</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose courage over comfort</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          The right decision and the comfortable decision are often different things. Fear keeps you in the safe zone. Love for what you're building — and who you're building it with — gives you the courage to make the harder call.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-3">02</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Lead with trust</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          Micromanagement is fear in action — fear that people won't deliver, that you'll lose control, that things will fall apart without you. Real leadership starts with defaulting to trust. It's not naive; it's a choice to lead from your best self.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-3">03</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Embrace growth</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          Fear wants to protect you from discomfort. But every setback, every difficult conversation, every thing that didn't go as planned is an opportunity to learn and evolve — if you're willing to stay open to it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-3">04</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Build from purpose</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          When the work is aligned with your values, everything changes. You attract the right people, you make clearer decisions, and you sustain momentum over the long run. Purpose is love made practical.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How David Lives It -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <SectionHeading title="How David Lives It" />
      <div class="space-y-5 text-base text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Love Not Fear shows up in how David runs his companies — in the hiring process, which prioritizes values alignment over credentials; in how he handles underperformance, with directness and care rather than avoidance or coldness; in how he builds leadership teams, with real trust and real ownership.
        </p>
        <p>
          It shows up in his coaching work with founders: most of the stuck points he sees aren't strategic — they're emotional. A founder who can't let go of a bad hire. A CEO who avoids hard conversations until they become crises. A leader who scales anxiety rather than culture. The Love Not Fear framework gives them a concrete way to recognize the pattern and choose differently.
        </p>
        <p>
          And it shows up in his daily practice — meditation, reflection, conscious leadership work — because the framework only holds if the person at the center is doing their own inner work. You can't lead from love if you haven't learned to recognize your own fear.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Explore Further / CTAs -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <SectionHeading
        title="Explore Further"
        subtitle="The Love Not Fear framework lives across several projects. Here's where to go next."
      />
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">

        <a
          href="https://lovenotfear.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="group flex items-start justify-between gap-6 p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white hover:border-neutral-400 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-200"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1 group-hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">
              lovenotfear.com
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
              The full Love Not Fear community, programs, and resources. Where the framework lives in the world.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 group-hover:text-neutral-700 transition-colors" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 6H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 003 8.25v10.5A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h10.5A2.25 2.25 0 0018 18.75V10.5m-10.5 6L21 3m0 0h-5.25M21 3v5.25" />
            </svg>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a
          href="https://lnfpeople.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="group flex items-start justify-between gap-6 p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white hover:border-neutral-400 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-200"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1 group-hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">
              lnfpeople.com
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
              Values-driven recruiting built on Love Not Fear principles. Find people who are the right fit — for who you are, not just what you need done.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 group-hover:text-neutral-700 transition-colors" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 6H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 003 8.25v10.5A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h10.5A2.25 2.25 0 0018 18.75V10.5m-10.5 6L21 3m0 0h-5.25M21 3v5.25" />
            </svg>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a
          href="/about"
          class="group flex items-start justify-between gap-6 p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg bg-white hover:border-neutral-400 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-200"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1 group-hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">
              About David
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
              The story behind the framework — 20+ years of building companies, inner work, and conscious leadership.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 group-hover:text-neutral-700 transition-colors" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
            </svg>
          </div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
